cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV, cs.CL

The paper presents a novel method for amortised inference in probabilistic programming languages using neural networks. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method also involves graphical models and probabilistic reasoning, which are relevant to systems and control (cs.SY). The use of neural networks for inference also has applications in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
